name: 2,3,4,5-tetrahydropyridine-2,6-dicarboxylate N-succinyltransferase
classes: Transferring groups other than aminoacyl groups
comment: Involved in the biosynthesis of lysine in bacteria (including cyanobacteria) and higher plants. The 1992 edition of the Enzyme List erroneously gave the name 2,3,4,5-tetrahydropyridine-2-carboxylate N-succinyltransferase to this enzyme.

references.title: Purification and characterization of succinyl-CoA: tetrahydrodipicolinate N-succinyltransferase from Escherichia coli.
